{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"3699C","heading":"High technology program","label":"3699C High technology program","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/ptIII/ch36/schIII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThe date of enactment of this section, referred to in subsec. (f), is the date of enactment of , which was approved .Pub. L. 118–210Jan. 2, 2025"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Establishment","label":"a .—Establishment","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall carry out a program under which the Secretary provides covered individuals with the opportunity to enroll in high technology programs of education that the Secretary determines provide training or skills sought by employers in a relevant field or industry.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not more than 4,000 covered individuals may participate in the program under this section in any fiscal year.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Amount of Assistance","label":"b .—Amount of Assistance","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall provide, to each covered individual who pursues a high technology program of education under this section, educational assistance in amounts equal to the amounts provided under , including, except as provided in paragraph (3), with respect to the housing stipend described in that section and in accordance with the treatment of programs that are distance learning and programs that are less than half-time.section 3313(c)(1) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/b/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fb%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A high technology program of education.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/b/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/b/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fb%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/b/2/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/b/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fb%2F2%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the second such program begins at least 18 months after the covered individual graduates from the first such program; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/b/2/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/b/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fb%2F2%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the covered individual uses educational assistance under chapter 33 of this title to pursue the second such program.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"No covered individual may receive a housing stipend under this subsection for any month if such individual is in receipt of a housing stipend under chapter 33 of this title for that month.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Contracts","label":"c .—Contracts","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"For purposes of carrying out subsection (a), the Secretary shall seek to enter into contracts with any number of qualified providers of high technology programs of education for the provision of such programs to covered individuals. Each such contract shall provide for the conditions under which the Secretary may terminate the contract with the provider and the procedures for providing for the graduation of students who were enrolled in a program provided by such provider in the case of such a termination.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"upon the enrollment of a covered individual in the program, 25 percent of the cost of the tuition and other fees for the program of education for the individual;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"upon graduation of the individual from the program, 25 percent of such cost; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/2/C/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/2/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F2%2FC%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/2/C/i/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/2/C/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F2%2FC%2Fi%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"of 180 days in the field of study of the program; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/2/C/i/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/2/C/i","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F2%2FC%2Fi%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"that begins not later than 180 days following graduation of the covered individual from the program;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/2/C/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/2/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F2%2FC%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the employment of the individual by the provider for a period of one year; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/2/C/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/2/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F2%2FC%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the enrollment of the individual in a program of education to continue education in such field of study.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the provider employs instructors whom the Secretary determines are experts in their respective fields in accordance with paragraph (5);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the provider has successfully provided the high technology program for at least one year;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/3/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F3%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the provider does not charge tuition and fees to a covered individual who receives assistance under this section to pursue such program that are higher than the tuition and fees charged by such provider to another individual; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/3/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F3%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the provider meets the approval criteria developed by the Secretary under paragraph (4).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/4/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F4%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall prescribe criteria for approving providers of a high technology program of education under this section.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/4/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F4%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In developing such criteria, the Secretary may consult with State approving agencies.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/4/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F4%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Such criteria are not required to meet the requirements of .section 3672 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/4/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F4%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Such criteria shall include the job placement rate, in the field of study of a program of education, of covered individuals who complete such program of education.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/5/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F5%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"identify professions in need of new employees to hire, tailor the programs to meet market needs, and identify the employers likely to hire graduates;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/5/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F5%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"effectively teach the skills offered to covered individuals;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/5/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F5%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"provide relevant industry experience in the fields of programs offered to incoming covered individuals; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/5/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F5%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"demonstrate relevant industry experience in such fields of programs.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/6/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F6%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"from which at least 70 percent of graduates find full-time employment in the field of study of the program during the 180-day period beginning on the date the student graduates from the program; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/6/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/c/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fc%2F6%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"that offers tuition reimbursement for any student who graduates from such a program and does not find employment described in subparagraph (A).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":".—Effect on Other Entitlement","label":"d .—Effect on Other Entitlement","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"If a covered individual enrolled in a high technology program of education under this section has remaining entitlement to educational assistance under chapter 30, 32, 33, 34, or 35 of this title, such entitlement shall be charged at the rate of one month of such entitlement for each month of educational assistance provided under this section.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"If a covered individual enrolled in a high technology program of education under this section does not have remaining entitlement to educational assistance under chapter 30, 32, 33, 34, or 35 of this title, any educational assistance provided to such individual under this section shall be provided in addition to the entitlement that the individual has used.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fd%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary may not consider enrollment in a high technology program of education under this section to be assistance under a provision of law referred to in .section 3695 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fd%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d/4/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fd%2F4%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d/4/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d/4/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fd%2F4%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"in the case of the enrollment of an individual referred to under paragraph (1), the amount of entitlement that is typically charged for such enrollment;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d/4/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d/4/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fd%2F4%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an identification of any methods that may be available for minimizing the amount of entitlement required for such enrollment; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d/4/A/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d/4/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fd%2F4%2FA%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an element requiring applicants to acknowledge receipt of the notice under this subparagraph.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d/4/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/d/4","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fd%2F4%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"If the Secretary approves the enrollment of a covered individual in a high technology program of education under this section, the Secretary shall deliver electronically to the individual an award letter that provides notice of such approval and includes specific information describing how paragraphs (1) and (2) will be applied to the individual if the individual chooses to enroll in the program.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":".—Requirements for Educational Institutions","label":"e .—Requirements for Educational Institutions","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fe%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall not approve the enrollment of any covered individual, not already enrolled, in any high technology programs of education under this section for any period during which the Secretary finds that more than 85 percent of the students enrolled in the program are having all or part of their tuition, fees, or other charges paid to or for them by the educational institution or by the Department of Veterans Affairs under this title or under chapter 1606 or 1607 of title 10, except with respect to tuition, fees, or other charges that are paid under a payment plan at an educational institution that the Secretary determines has a history of offering payment plans that are completed not later than 180 days after the end of the applicable term, quarter, or semester.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fe%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary may waive a requirement of paragraph (1) if the Secretary determines, pursuant to regulations which the Secretary shall prescribe, such waiver to be in the interest of the covered individual and the Federal Government. Not later than 30 days after the Secretary waives such a requirement, the Secretary shall submit to the Committees on Veterans’ Affairs of the Senate and House of Representatives a report regarding such waiver.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fe%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fe%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e/3/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fe%2F3%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall establish and maintain a process by which an educational institution may request a review of a determination that the educational institution does not meet the requirements of paragraph (1).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e/3/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fe%2F3%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary may consult with a State approving agency regarding such process or such a review.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e/3/A/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e/3/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fe%2F3%2FA%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Not later than 180 days after the Secretary establishes or revises a process under this subparagraph, the Secretary shall submit to the Committees on Veterans’ Affairs of the Senate and House of Representatives a report regarding such process.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fe%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e/3/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fe%2F3%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"shall request the review not later than 30 days after the start of the term, quarter, or semester for which the determination described in subparagraph (A) applies; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e/3/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/e/3/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fe%2F3%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"may include any information that the educational institution believes the Department should have taken into account when making the determination, including with respect to any mitigating circumstances.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":".—Annual Reports","label":"f .—Annual Reports","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/f/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Ff%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The number of covered individuals enrolled in the program, disaggregated by type of educational institution, during the year covered by the report.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/f/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Ff%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The number of covered individuals who completed a high technology program of education under the program during the year covered by the report.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/f/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Ff%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The average employment rate of covered individuals who completed such a program of education during such year, as of 180 days after the date of completion.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/f/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Ff%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The average length of time between the completion of such a program of education and employment.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/f/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Ff%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The total number of covered individuals who completed a program of education under the program and who, as of the date of the submission of the report, are employed in a position related to technology.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/f/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Ff%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The average salary of a covered individual who completed a program of education under the program and who is employed in a position related to technology, in various geographic areas determined by the Secretary.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":null,"label":"7","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/f/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Ff%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The average salary of all individuals employed in positions related to technology in the geographic areas determined under subparagraph (F), and the difference, if any, between such average salary and the average salary of a covered individual who completed a program of education under the program and who is employed in a position related to technology.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"8","heading":null,"label":"8","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/f/8","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Ff%2F8","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The number of covered individuals who completed a program of education under the program and who subsequently enrolled in a second program of education under the program.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"g","heading":".—Collection of Information; Consultation","label":"g .—Collection of Information; Consultation","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/g","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fg","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/g/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fg%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall develop practices to use to collect information about covered individuals and providers of high technology programs of education.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/g/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/g","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fg%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"For the purpose of carrying out program under this section, the Secretary may consult with providers of high technology programs of education and may establish an advisory group made up of representatives of such providers, private employers in the technology field, and other relevant groups or entities, as the Secretary determines necessary.1","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"h","heading":".—Definitions","label":"h .—Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fh","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fh%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fh%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/1/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fh%2F1%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"served an aggregate of at least 36 months on active duty in the Armed Forces (including service on active duty in entry level and skill training) and was discharged or released therefrom under conditions other than dishonorable; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/1/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fh%2F1%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"has not attained the age of 62.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fh%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A member of the Armed Forces that the Secretary determines will become a veteran described in subparagraph (A) fewer than 180 days after the date of such determination.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fh%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fh%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"offered by a public or private educational institution;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fh%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"if offered by an institution of higher learning, that is provided directly by such institution rather than by an entity other than such institution under a contract or other agreement;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fh%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"that does not lead to a degree;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fh%2F2%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"that has a term of not less than six and not more than 28 weeks; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/2/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fh%2F2%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":".—Termination","label":"i .—Termination","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/2/E/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t38/s3699C/h/2/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft38%2Fs3699C%2Fh%2F2%2FE%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary may not provide educational assistance under this section for a high technology program of education that begins after .September 30, 2027","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}]}]}
